How is a queue implemented? Provide an example using a linked list.

[ANswer]
A queue can be implemented using various data structures like arrays, linked lists, or circular buffers. Here's an example using a singly-linked list:

```c++
struct Node {
    int data;
    Node* next;
};

struct Queue {
    Node* front;
    Node* rear;
};

void enqueue(Queue* q, int value) {
    Node* newNode = new Node();
    newNode->data = value;
    newNode->next = NULL;

    if (q->rear == NULL) {
        q->front = q->rear = newNode;
    } else {
        q->rear->next = newNode;
        q->rear = newNode;
    }
}
```



